    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>San Francisco</placeName>
                <date>Oct 4 1859</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Dear friend—</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">I have duly recd your<lb/> Letter of the <date>11th</date> ulto also
                the list of your debtors for<lb/> the subscription of the “Occident”</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I send you enclosed sight Draft on<lb/>
                <persName>Drexel &amp; Co</persName> for $65.20 for which I have paid<lb/> 2%
                exchange making $1.30¢ which together amount<lb/> to $66.50, being the amount I have
                collected<lb/> for the subscription of the “Occident” as follows:</p>
            <table cols="3" rows="12">
                <row>
                    <cell>
                        <persName>M. Mayblum</persName>
                    </cell>
                    <cell>
                        <placeName>San Francisco</placeName>
                    </cell>
                    <cell>$3.00</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>
                        <persName>H. Neustadter</persName>
                    </cell>
                    <cell>“</cell>
                    <cell>5.—</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>
                        <persName>D. Stern</persName>
                    </cell>
                    <cell>“</cell>
                    <cell>5.—</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>
                        <persName>Samuel Marx</persName>
                    </cell>
                    <cell>“</cell>
                    <cell>9.—</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>
                        <persName>Hamburger Brothers</persName>
                    </cell>
                    <cell>“</cell>
                    <cell>10.—</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>
                        <persName>L. Tichner</persName>
                    </cell>
                    <cell>“</cell>
                    <cell>6.—</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>
                        <persName>Scholle Bros</persName>
                    </cell>
                    <cell>“</cell>
                    <cell>7.50</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>
                        <persName>Lazard Freres</persName>
                    </cell>
                    <cell>“</cell>
                    <cell>9.—</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>
                        <persName>H. W. Stein</persName>
                    </cell>
                    <cell>“</cell>
                    <cell>3.—</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>
                        <persName>Jules Cerf</persName>
                    </cell>
                    <cell>“</cell>
                    <cell>6.—</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>
                        <persName>J. A. Brunner</persName>
                    </cell>
                    <cell>“ 1 year adv.</cell>
                    <cell>
                        <hi rend="underline">3.—</hi>
                    </cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>(making the above mentioned sum)</cell>
                    <cell/>
                    <cell>$66.50</cell>
                </row>
            </table>
            <p rend="indent(1)">You will perceive that the most of mentioned<lb/> payments are not
                in full, as I have followed<lb/> out your requests &amp; have compromised with</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>all those who complained that they did not<lb/> receive the “Occidents” regularly,
                that they never<lb/> ordered them, that they gave notice for a<lb/> discontinuation
                &amp;c &amp;c. &amp; I have deemed it<lb/> to be your benefit to comply with your
                request<lb/> &amp; took all I could get from the parties.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">You have <persName>Mr Mayblum</persName> down for 2 years;<lb/> he
                says that he recd the “Occident” in the capacity<lb/> of <placeName>South
                    Carolina</placeName> of Post Master &amp; as such did<lb/> not think himself
                liable for any subscription &amp;c<lb/> therefore I have compromised it for
                $3.00</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">$5.00 is all I could collect from <persName>H
                Neustadter</persName>;<lb/> says that he did not wish the Occid for<lb/> some time;
                he <hi rend="underline">wishes to stop his subscription</hi><lb/> The same remark is
                applicable to <persName>D. Stern</persName></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mr Saml Hart</persName> wishes all the back<lb/> Nos since
                the weekly has been commenced</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Hamburger Bros</persName> think they cannot owe<lb/> you
                $15.00, still if you were sure they will<lb/> pay the Balance of $5.00</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">$7.50 was the most I could draw from <persName>Scholle<lb/>
                    Bros</persName>; they wish the “Occident” no more.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>H. W. Stern</persName> makes the reason for paying<lb/>
                less, not receiving it &amp; <add>?</add>; he also wishes to<lb/> discontinue his
                subscription</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mr S. T. Meyer</persName>, whom you have on the<lb/> list
                resides now at <placeName>New York</placeName>; <persName>Mr Aaron<lb/>
                    Jacobs</persName> there can tell you where he can be<lb/> found. <persName>Jules
                    Cerf</persName> makes also the excuse</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>not having subscribed &amp; <add>?</add> he wishes to dis-<lb/>-continue his
                subscription, you will observe<lb/> that I also settled with him.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Since you gave me authority to settle<lb/> with the parties who made
                excuses &amp; complaints<lb/> to escape payments, I have used it, &amp;<lb/> with my
                most active endeavors in your<lb/> behalf have I worked to make these
                collections,<lb/> &amp; I trust you will approve of my work.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I would beg leave to suggest to you to<lb/> stop always the
                subscription when desired,<lb/> as you cannot afford to supply people<lb/> with
                papers without their wishes &amp; payments.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Please do not forget to acknowledge<lb/> in your next issue all the
                various<lb/> payments as collected; as I have not given<lb/> any receipts, save in a
                single instance.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Please accept the following new<lb/> subscribers I got:
                        <persName><hi rend="underline">Lewis Cohn</hi></persName>, <placeName>San
                    Francisco</placeName><lb/>
                <persName>J. A. <hi rend="underline">Bruner</hi></persName>, <placeName>San
                    Francisco</placeName>, (the latter<lb/> gentleman has paid one year's
                subscription<lb/> in advance, which you will observe amongst<lb/> the list of
                collections) <persName><hi rend="underline">Regensburger</hi><lb/>
                    <hi rend="underline">&amp; Stern</hi></persName>
                <placeName>San Francisco</placeName>, whose subscription<lb/> is in place of
                    <persName>D Stern</persName> (discontinued)</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mr Alexander Mayer</persName> who arrived<lb/> here in
                safety from <placeName>Phil</placeName> requests me to<lb/> state that he has sold
                all the bibles save<lb/> one. <persName>Mr Jacob Bloomingdale</persName> whom</p>
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p>you have on the list lives now in<lb/>
                <placeName>Germany</placeName> think <placeName>Frankfort</placeName>. I see that
                you have<lb/>
                <persName>Haas</persName> &amp; <persName>Rosenfeld</persName> on the list for
                $15.00, which<lb/> is doubtful that I will be able to collect<lb/> as on their last
                payment they requested<lb/> a discontinuance, of which I wrote you<lb/> at the time.
                    <persName>Raphael Schoyer</persName> is<lb/> not in the city, he left for
                    <placeName>Japan</placeName>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>S. Fleishhacker</persName> resides at
                    <placeName>Placerville</placeName><lb/> &amp; I hope you will not send him<lb/>
                the “Occident” as you can never ex-<lb/>-pect a cent from him, being too fond<lb/>
                of whiskey &amp; rum. <persName>Hess</persName> lives in <placeName>N
                    York</placeName>.<lb/> where <persName>Cha-Simon</persName> is I cannot
                tell,<lb/> you better therefore discontinue sending<lb/> the “Occid” to him. From
                    <persName>F. M.<lb/> Reinhart</persName> I cannot collect anything; he<lb/>
                lives here now &amp; am well acquainted<lb/> with him. <persName>Aaron
                    Rosenheim</persName> does not<lb/> live anymore at
                <placeName>Nevada</placeName>, he resides<lb/> here now; I think his Brother lives
                there<lb/> yet. You are wrong in believing <del>then</del><lb/>
                <persName>Aaron Rosenheim</persName> rich.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I have made those collections<lb/> all myself; time did not allow
                me<lb/> to call on every one as yet, but shall<lb/> do so as soon as I shall have
                some</p>
        </body>
    </text>
